### Test Missing Customer Attributes
### This will help us debug why some attributes are missing from the response

### Step 1: Get current customer info (to see what's missing)
GET https://localhost:5001/customer/info
Authorization: Bearer eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsImtpZCI6IlRYbCJ9..dIo_yJBep4DMgxFh_iOFyTyoz70GUh8j2jZaJl5H_Uw
Accept: application/json

###

### Step 2: Update customer with ALL new attributes
PUT https://localhost:5001/customer/info
Authorization: Bearer eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsImtpZCI6IlRYbCJ9..dIo_yJBep4DMgxFh_iOFyTyoz70GUh8j2jZaJl5H_Uw
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Lisa Updated",
  "phoneNumber": "+1-555-0123",
  "membershipStatus": "premium",
  "membershipExpiryDate": "2025-12-31T23:59:59Z",
  "address": "123 Test Street, Apt 4B",
  "postalCode": "12345",
  "city": "Test City"
}

###

### Step 3: Get customer info again (should now show all attributes)
GET https://localhost:5001/customer/info
Authorization: Bearer eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsImtpZCI6IlRYbCJ9..dIo_yJBep4DMgxFh_iOFyTyoz70GUh8j2jZaJl5H_Uw
Accept: application/json

# This should now include:
# - membershipStatus: "premium"
# - membershipExpiryDate: "2025-12-31T23:59:59Z"
# - address: "123 Test Street, Apt 4B"
# - postalCode: "12345"
# - city: "Test City"

###

### Step 4: Test partial update (only membership)
PUT https://localhost:5001/customer/info
Authorization: Bearer eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsImtpZCI6IlRYbCJ9..dIo_yJBep4DMgxFh_iOFyTyoz70GUh8j2jZaJl5H_Uw
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "membershipStatus": "gold"
}

###

### Step 5: Final check - get customer info
GET https://localhost:5001/customer/info
Authorization: Bearer eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsImtpZCI6IlRYbCJ9..dIo_yJBep4DMgxFh_iOFyTyoz70GUh8j2jZaJl5H_Uw
Accept: application/json

# Should show:
# - membershipStatus: "gold" (updated)
# - membershipExpiryDate: "2025-12-31T23:59:59Z" (preserved)
# - address: "123 Test Street, Apt 4B" (preserved)
# - postalCode: "12345" (preserved)
# - city: "Test City" (preserved)

###

### Expected Behavior:
# 1. Initially, new attributes might be null/missing (ServiceStack excludes nulls by default)
# 2. After Step 2 update, ALL new attributes should appear in response
# 3. After Step 4 partial update, all attributes should still be present
# 4. This confirms the database columns exist and the API is working correctly
